<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - TROUBLESHOOTING - SPEEDOMETER SENSOR AND CIRCUITS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SPEEDOMETER SENSOR AND CIRCUITS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08035x_10.xml" xrefid="x0803505">SPEEDOMETER</hotlnk>
                for operation description of speedometer circuits.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x080355a">
            <title>Inspecting And Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS)</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect engine harness connector from the sensor. Loosen the locknut and remove the
                    sensor. The harness connector and sensor should be free of damage or corrosion. Remove any metal
                    shavings or debris from the sensor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install the sensor, turn in until the sensor contacts the transmission speedometer
                    gear, then back out
                    <emph type="bold">one full turn.</emph>
                    Tighten lock nut to 15 ft-lbs. (20.3 N&#183; m). This assures that the sensor is adjusted properly
                    for the next test.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>To perform this test, construct two test leads using terminals (P/N 1680205C1) and suitable length of
                16GA wire. Install terminals on one end and alligator clips on the other.
            </para>
            <table id="t0803510" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing the VSS</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.34in"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>With VSS disconnected, use test lead to measure resistance to ground at both
                                    <emph type="bold">sensor</emph>
                                    terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Sensor terminals to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>> or = 100K Ohms</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Replace the VSS (refer to paragraphs above).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Use test leads and measure resistance between VSS sensor terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Between sensor terminals</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>600 to 900 Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Replace the VSS (refer to paragraphs above).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Perform sensor output test below.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.0 AC Volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>VSS checks good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Replace the VSS.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <title>VSS Sensor Output Test</title>
            </para>
            <para>This test checks for proper AC voltage output from the VSS sensor. Improper adjustment will cause LOW,
                ERRATIC, or NO sensor output.
            </para>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Block front wheels and place rear axles on floor stands.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Use AC voltmeter with sufficient length leads to avoid personal contact with rotating vehicle
                        wheels during this test. Connect meter leads to test leads.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Run engine at idle speed, with transmission in high gear. Measure voltage across the two
                        sensor terminals.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Sensor output should be 2.0 AC volts or more.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Signal To Speedo/Tach Module (Mechanical Engine Only)</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>To test Vehicle Speed Sensor circuits to the ECM with electronic engines, refer to Group 08 -
                        Electronic Engine Controls in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Perform
                <hotlnk xrefid="x080355a">Inspecting and Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor</hotlnk>
                before performing this test!
            </para>
            <table id="t0803511" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Signal To Speedo/Tach Module (Mechanical Engine Only)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.55in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.84in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.36in"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Remove connector (421) from Speedo/ Tach module and disconnect engine harness
                                    connector (88) from the vehicle speed sensor. At connector (421) measure resistance
                                    to ground at circuits 47A and 47B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(421) circuits 47A and 47B to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>> or = 100K Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit with less than 100K resistance, between
                                    connectors (421) and (88), then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>At connector (421) measure resistance between circuits 47A and 47B and between all
                                    other circuits in the connector.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(421) circuits 47A and 47B and all other circuits</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>> or = 100K Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Locate short between any circuits with less than 100K resistance between
                                    terminals, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>At connector (88) use test lead to jumper circuit 47A to ground. At connector
                                    (421) measure resistance to ground at circuit 47A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(421)</para>
                                <para>circuit 47A to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 47A between connectors (421) to (88), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>At connector (88) use test lead to jumper circuit 47B to ground. At connector
                                    (421) measure resistance to ground at circuit 47B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(421)</para>
                                <para>circuit 47B to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 47B between connectors (88) and (421), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>The vehicle speed sensor and connecting circuits check good. If speedometer and
                                    tachometer gauges were switched (see
                                    <hotlnk document="s08035x_40.xml" xrefid="x0803508">GAUGE CIRCUIT
                                        TROUBLESHOOTING</hotlnk>) then replace the Speedo/Tach module.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
